---
import "./index.scss";
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from "../consts";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>saito.style</h1>
    <header>
      <p>Hi! I am Carlos Saito</p>
      <p>
        I work as a developer at KTH (Royal Institute of Technology) in
        Stockholm
      </p>
      <p>
        I was hired initially as “Full-stack developer” and I’m pivoting
        recently to a more “UX engineer” role
      </p>
    </header>
    <main>
      <h2>Projects when I worked at KTH (2018-2024)</h2>
      <section>
        <div>
          <h3>Design system "KTH Style" and new visual identity</h3>
          <dl>
            <dt>Role</dt>
            <dd>UX enginner</dd>
            <dt>Date</dt>
            <dd>2023-2024</dd>
          </dl>
        </div>
        <p>
          KTH has a new visual identity. The IT department and the web team was
          in charge of leading the digital side of the evolution.
        </p>
        <p>
          Design and prototype: co-organised design workshops with UX designers,
          copywriters and stakeholders and understand problems to solve, their
          needs and their opinions; prototyped and designed the first pieces of
          the new identity (the website header).
        </p>
        <p>
          Implementation: created a new version of the KTH Design System “KTH
          Style” and helped other teams to implement the new design
        </p>
        <h4>Challenges</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>The new version of KTH Style is no longer based on Bootstrap</li>
          <li>
            Create a library retro-compatible with the old version so teams can
            upgrade in small steps
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h4>Design principles</h4>
        <p>The new version of KTH Style is</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Modular: instead of importing the whole library (including parts
            outside of developers control), developers choose what parts to
            import
          </li>
          <li>
            Simple: the new version has less code and does not create unused
            abstractions
          </li>
          <li>Systematic: everything is defined as tokens (variables)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </main>
    <aside>
      <h2>past work experience</h2>
      <h3>COAM (Official College of Architects of Madrid)</h3>
      <p>
        Developer of “Revista Arquitectura”, the web of the COAM’s magazine.
